    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>We are heavily using <a href=\"http://easymock.org\" rel=\"noreferrer\">EasyMock</a> and EasyMock Class Extension at work and are pretty happy with it. It basically gives you everything you need. Take a look at the documentation, there's a very nice example which shows you all the features of EasyMock.</p>\n"
