    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Mockito also provides the option of stubbing methods, matching arguments (like anyInt() and anyString()), verifying the number of invocations (times(3), atLeastOnce(), never()), <a href=\"http://mockito.googlecode.com/svn/branches/1.5/javadoc/org/mockito/Mockito.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">and more</a>.</p>\n\n<p>I've also found that Mockito is <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/22697/whats-the-best-mock-framework-for-java#23048\">simple and clean</a>.</p>\n\n<p>One thing I don't like about Mockito is that you <a href=\"http://code.google.com/p/mockito/wiki/FAQ\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">can't stub static methods</a>.</p>\n"
