      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1429198780,
      "post_id" : 1024869,
      "comment_id" : 47496421,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I am impressed by JMockit, it has a steeper learning curve, but it has very good documentation for years, and it can mock anything. I started with Mockito, which was easy to learn, but I regularly met problems which I could not solve with it. On the other hand I cannot even imagine what is impossible with JMockit."
